Logs and metrics are collected on the platform and application levels of Cloud Foundry (CF) deployments. The following sources collect CF logs and metrics:

- **Loggregator**: Loggregator collects logs and metrics from applications. It also collects metrics from CF components on the platform level. For more information about the Loggregator system, including Loggregator architecture and components, see [Overview of the Loggregator System](./architecture.html).
- **CF components**: CF components collect logs on the platform level. On Linux machines, this collection process is faciliated by rsyslogd.

