##About Logs and Metrics

The types of information included in logs and metrics vary based on the CF deployment level.

Metrics include the following content:

- **Platform Level**: Metrics on the platform level include measurements of CF platform components as well as system metrics from VMs. For more information about collecting metrics on VMs using the BOSH Health Monitor, see [Configuring a Monitoring System](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/monitoring/metrics.html#bosh-cf).
- **Application Level**: Metrics on the application level include container metrics, such as CPU, memory, and disk usage. They also include custom metrics configured by the user. For more information about configuring an application to emit custom metrics to Loggregator, see [Metrics Forwarder for PCF] (https://docs.pivotal.io/metrics-forwarder/).

Logs include the following content:

- **Platform Level**: Logs on the platform level incude every system event logged by CF platform components.
- **Application Level**: Logs on the application level include all application process events. For more information about application logging, see [Application Logging in Cloud Foundry](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/devguide/deploy-apps/streaming-logs.html).

